\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15095451 
\par The Life of our Holy Mother Mary of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Egypt{\*\xmlclose}  - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15552528 Page }{\field{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15552528  PAGE }}{\fldrslt {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid13046565 27}}}\sectd \linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15552528  of }{\field{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15552528  NUMPAGES }
}{\fldrslt {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang1024\langfe1024\noproof\insrsid13046565 52}}}\sectd \linex0\endnhere\sectdefaultcl\sftnbj {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15095451 
\par }}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s24\qc \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\ai\af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\i\f1\fs32\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid4199946 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 The Life of our Holy Mother Mary of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Egypt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 {\*\xmlclose}
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Second Half}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s23\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s23\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1256504 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
Having repeated my attempt three or four times, at last I felt exhausted and had no more strength to push and to be pushed, so I went aside and stood in a corner of the porch. And only then with great difficulty it began to dawn on me, and I began to unde
r
stand the reason why I was prevented from being admitted to see the life-giving Cross. The word of salvation gently touched the eyes of my heart and revealed to me that it was my unclean life which barred the entrance to me. I began to weep and lament and
 beat my breast, and to sigh from the depths of my heart. And so I stood weeping when I saw above me the icon of the most holy Mother of God. And turning to her my bodily and spiritual eyes I said: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 `O Lady, Mother of God, who gave birth in the flesh to Go
d the Word, I know, O how well I know, that it is no honor or praise to thee when one so impure and depraved as I look up to thy icon, O ever-virgin, who didst keep thy body and soul in purity. Rightly do I inspire hatred and disgust before thy virginal p
u
rity. But I have heard that God Who was born of thee became man on purpose to call sinners to repentance. Then help me, for I have no other help. Order the entrance of the church to be opened to me. Allow me to see the venerable Tree on which He Who was b
o
rn of thee suffered in the flesh and on which He shed His holy Blood for the redemption of sinners and for me, unworthy as I am. Be my faithful witness before thy son that I will never again defile my body by the impurity of fornication, but as soon as I 
have seen the Tree of the Cross I will renounce the world and its temptations and will go wherever thou wilt lead me.' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Thus I spoke and as if acquiring some hope in firm faith and feeling some confidence in the mercy of the Mother of God, I left the place
 where I stood praying. And I went again and mingled with the crowd that was pushing its way into the temple. And no one seemed to thwart me, no one hindered my entering the church. I was possessed with trembling, and was almost in delirium. Having got as
 
far as the doors which I could not reach before -- as if the same force which had hindered me cleared the way for me -- I now entered without difficulty and found myself within the holy place. And so it was I saw the life-giving Cross. I saw too the Myste
ries of God and how the Lord accepts repentance. Throwing myself on the ground, I worshipped that holy earth and kissed it with trembling. The}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid1065548 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147  I came out of the church and went to her who had promised to be my security, to the place where I had sealed my v
ow. And bending my knees before the Virgin Mother of God, I addressed to her such words as these: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 `O loving Lady, thou hast shown me thy great love for all men. Glory to God W
ho receives the repentance of sinners through thee. What more can I recollect or say, I who am so sinful? It is time for me, O Lady to fulfill my vow, according to thy witness. Now lead me by the hand along the path of repentance!' And at these words I he
ard a voice from on high: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 `If you cross the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose} you will find glorious rest.' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Hearing this voice and having faith that it was for me, I cried to the Mother of God: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 `O Lady, Lady, do not forsake me!' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 With these words I left the porch of the church and set off on my journey. As I was leaving the church a stranger glanced at me and gave me three coins, saying: }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 `Sister, take these.' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And, taking the money, I bought three loaves and took them with me on my journey, as a blessed gift. I asked the person who sold the bread: `Which is the way to the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}?' I was directed to the city gate which led that way. Running on I passed the gates and still weeping went on my journey. Those I met I asked the way, and after walking for
 the rest of that day (I think it was nine o'clock when I saw the Cross) I at length reached at sunset the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Church{\*\xmlclose} of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}St. John{\*\xmlclose}
 the Baptist which stood on the banks of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}. After praying in the temple, I went down to the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
 and rinsed my face and hands in its holy waters. I partook of the holy and life-giving Mysteries in the Church of the Forerunner and ate half of one of my loaves. Then, after drinking some water from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan
{\*\xmlclose}, I
 lay down and passed the night on the ground. In the morning I found a small boat and crossed to the opposite bank. I again prayed to Our Lady to lead me whither she wished. Then I found myself in this desert and since then up to this very day I am estran
ged from all, keeping away from people and running away from everyone. And I live here clinging to my God Who saves all who turn to Him from faintheartedness and storms." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas asked her: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "How many years have gone by since you began to live in this desert?" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 She replied: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Forty-seven years have already gone by, I think, since I left the holy city." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas asked: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "But what food do you find?" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 The woman said: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "I had two and a half loaves when I crossed the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}. Soon they dried
 up and became hard as rock. Eating a little I gradually finished them after a few years." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas asked. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Can it be that without getting ill you have lived so many years thus, without suffering in any way from such a complete change?" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 The woman answered: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
"You remind me, Zosimas, of what I dare not speak of. For when I recall all the dangers which I overcame, and all the violent thoughts which confused me, I am again afraid that they will take possession of me." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas said: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Do not hide from me anything; speak to me without concealing anything." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And she said to him: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Believe me, Abba, seventeen years I passed in this desert fighting wild beasts -- mad desires and passions. When I was about to partake of food, I used to begin t
o regret the meat and fish of which I had so much in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Egypt{\*\xmlclose}
. I regretted also not having wine which I loved so much. For I drank a lot of wine when I lived in the world, while here I had not even water. I used to burn and succumb with thirst. 
The mad desire for profligate songs also entered me and confused me greatly, edging me on to sing satanic songs which I had learned once. But when such desires entered me I struck myself on the breast and reminded myself of the vow which I had made, when 
g
oing into the desert. In my thoughts I returned to the icon of the Mother of God which had received me and to her I cried in prayer. I implored her to chase away the thoughts to which my miserable soul was succumbing. And after weeping for long and beatin
g my breast I used to see light at last which seemed to shine on me from everywhere. And after the violent storm, lasting calm descended. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And how can I tell you about the thoughts which urged me on to fornication, how can I express them to you, Abba? A fi
re was kindled in my miserable heart which seemed to burn me up completely and to awake in me a thirst for embraces. As soon as this craving came to me, I flung myself on the earth and watered it with my tears, as if I saw before me my witness, who had ap
p
eared to me in my disobedience, and who seemed to threaten punishment for the crime. And I did not rise from the ground (sometimes I lay thus prostrate for a day and a night) until a calm and sweet light descended and enlightened me and chased away the th
o
ughts that possessed me. But always I turned to the eyes of my mind to my Protectress, asking her to extend help to one who was sinking fast in the waves of the desert. And I always had her as my Helper and the Accepter of my repentance. And thus I lived 
for seventeen years amid constant dangers. And since then even till now the Mother of God helps me in everything and leads me as it were by the hand." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas asked: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Can it be that you did not need food and clothing?" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 She answered: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1256504 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "After finishing the loaves I had, of which I spoke, for seventeen years I have fed on herbs and all that can be found in the desert. The clothes I had when I crossed the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose} became torn and worn out. I suffered greatly from the cold and greatly from the extreme heat. At times the sun burned me up and at other times I shivered from the frost, and frequently falling to the ground I lay wi}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs32\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 thout breath and without motion. I struggled with many afflictions and with terrible temptations. But from that time till now the power of God in numerous ways ha}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs32\f36\fs32\insrsid3691649 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs32\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
 guarded my sinful soul and my humble body. When I only reflect on the evils from which Our Lord has delivered me I have imperishable food for hope o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs32\f36\fs32\insrsid3691649 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs32\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147  salvation. I am fed and clothe
d by the all-powerful Word of God, the Lord of all. For it is not by bread alone that man lives. And those who have stripped off the rags of sin have no refuge, hiding themselves in the clefts of the rocks }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs34\f36\fs16\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 (Job 24; Heb. 11:38)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 ." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s23\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1256504 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Hearing that she cited words }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid3691649 of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
Scripture, from Moses and Job, Zosimas asked her: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "And so you have read the psalms and other books?" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 She smiled at this and said to the elder: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Believe be, I have not seen a human face ever since I crossed the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
, except yours today. I have not seen a beast or a living being ever since I came into the desert. I never learned from books. I have never even heard anyone who sang and read from them. But the word of God which is alive and active, by itself teaches a m
an knowledge. And so this is the end of my tale. But, as I asked you in the beginning, so even now I implore you for the sake of the Incarnate word of God, to pray to the Lord for me who am such a sinner." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Thus concluding her tale she bowed down before him. And with tears the elder exclaimed: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
"Blessed is God Who creates the great and wondrous, the glorious and marvelous without end. Blessed is God Who has shown me how He rewards those who fear Him. Truly, O Lord, Thou dost not forsake those who seek Thee!" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And the woman, not allowing the elder to bow down before her, said: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
"I beg you, holy father, for the sake of Jesus Christ our God and Savior, tell no one what you have heard, until God delivers me of this earth. And now depart in peace and again nex
t year you shall see me, and I you, if God will preserve us in His great mercy. But for God's sake, do as I ask you. Next year during Lent do not cross the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
, as is your custom in the monastery." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas was amazed to hear that she know the rules of the monastery and could only say: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Glory to God Who bestows great gifts on those who love Him." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 She continued: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Remain, Abba, in the monastery. And even if you wish to depart, you will not be to do so. And at sunset of the holy day of 
the Last Supper, put some of the life-giving Body and Blood of Christ into a holy vessel worthy to hold such Mysteries for me, and bring it. And wait for me on the banks of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
 adjoining the inhabited parts of the land, so that I can come and partake of the life-giving Gifts. For, since the time I communicated in the temple of the Forerunner before crossing the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
 even to this day I have not approached the Holy Mysteries. And I thirst for them with irrepressible love a
nd longing. and therefore I ask and implore you to grant me my wish, bring me the life-giving Mysteries at the very hour when Our Lord made His disciples partake of His Divine Supper. Tell John the Abbot of the monastery where you live: Look to yourself a
nd to your brothers, for there is much that needs correction. Only do not say this now, but when God guides you. Pray for me!" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 With these words she vanished in the depths of the desert. And Zosimas, falling down on his knees and bowing down to the ground 
on which she had stood, sent up glory and thanks to God. And, after wandering thorough the desert, he returned to the monastery on the day all the brothers returned. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 For the whole year he kept silent, not daring to tell anyone of what he had seen. But in
 his soul he prayed to God to give him another chance of seeing the ascetic's dear face. And when at length the first Sunday of the Great Fast came, all went out into the desert with the customary prayers and the singing of psalms. Only Zosimas was held b
ack by illness -- he lay in a fever. And then he remembered what the saint had said to him: "and even if you wish to depart, you will not be able to do so." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Many days passed and at last recovering from his illness he remained in the monastery. And when ag
ain the monks returned and the day of the Last Supper dawned, he did as he had been ordered. And placing some of the most pure Body and Blood into a small chalice and putting some grapes and dates and lentils soaked in water into a small basket, he depart
ed for the desert and reached the banks of the Jordan and sat down to wait for the saint. He waited for a long while and then began to doubt. Then raising his eyes to heaven, he began to pray: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Grant me O Lord, to behold that which Thou hast allowed be to behold once. Do not let me depart in vain, bearing the burden of my sins." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And then another thought struck him: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "And what if she does come? There is no boat; how will she cross the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose} to come to me who am so unworthy?" }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
And as he was pondering thus he saw the holy woman appear and stand on the other side of the river. Zosimas got up rejoicing and glorifying and thanking God. And again the thought came to him that she could not cross the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}. Then he saw that she made the sign of the Cross over the waters of the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
 (and the night was a moonlight one, as he related afterwards) and then she at once stepped on to the waters and began walking across the surface towards him. And when he wanted to prostrate himself, she cried to him while still walking on the water: }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "What are you doing, Abba, you are a priest and carrying the divine Gifts!" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 He obeyed her and on reaching the shore she said to the elder: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Bless, father, bless me!" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 He answered her trembling, for a state of confusion had overcome him at the sight of the miracle: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Truly God did not lie when He promised that when we purify ourselves we shall be like Him. Glory to Thee, Christ our God, Who has shown me through thi
s thy slave how far away I stand from perfection." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
Here the woman asked him to say the Creed and our Father. He began, she finished the prayer and according to the custom of that time gave him the kiss of peace on the lips. Having partaken of the Holy My
steries, she raised her hands to heaven and sighed with tears in her eyes, exclaiming: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Now lettest Thou Thy servant depart in peace, O Lord, according to Thy word; for my eyes have seen Thy salvation." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Then she said to the elder: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Forgive me, Abba, for asking you, but fulfill another wish of mine. Go now to the monastery and let God's grace guard you. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid3691649 A}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 nd next year come again to the same place where I first met you. Come for God's sake, for you shall again see me, for such is the will of God." }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 He said to her: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "From this day on I would like to follow you and always see your holy face. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid3691649 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 ut now fulfill the one and only wish of an old man and take a little of the food I have brought for you." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
And he showed her the basket, while she just touched the lentils with the tips of her fingers, and taking three grains said that the Holy Spirit guards the substance of the soul unpolluted. Then she said: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Pray, for God's sake pray for me and remember a miserable wretch." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
Touching the saint's feet and asking for her prayers for the Church, the kingdom and himself, he let her depart with tears, while he went off sighing and sorrowful, for he could not hope to vanquish the invincible. Meanwhile she again 
made the sign of the Cross over the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose}
, and stepped on to the waters and crossed over as before. And the elder returned filled with joy and terror, accusing himself of not having asked the saint her name. But he decided to do so next year. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And when another year had passed, he again went into the desert. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid13046565\charrsid1593147 He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 reached the same spot but could see no sign of anyone. so raising his eyes to heaven as before, he prayed: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Show me, O Lord, Thy pure treasure, which Thou hast concealed in the desert. Show me, I pray Thee, the angel in the flesh, of which the world is not worthy." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Then on the opposite bank of the river, her face turned towards the rising sun, he saw the saint lying dead. Her hands were crossed according to custom and her face was t
urned to the East. Running up he shed tears over the saint's feet and kissed them, not daring to touch anything else. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 For a long time he wept. Then reciting the appointed psalms, he said the burial prayers and thought to himself: "Must I bury the body of
 a saint? Or will this be contrary to her wishes?" And then he saw words traced on the ground by her head: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1256504 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\cs41\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "Abba Zosimas, bury on this spot the body of humble Mary. Return to dust that which is dust and pray to the Lord for me, who departed in the month 
of Fermoutin of Egypt, called April by the Romans, on the first day, on the very night of our Lord's Passion, after having partaken of the Divine Mysteries." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs34\f36\fs16\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
[St. Mary died in 522 A. D.]}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\fs32\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s23\qj \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sl360\slmult1\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid1256504 \rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs32\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs32\cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 
\ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Reading this the elder was glad to know the saint's name. He understood too that as soon as she had partaken of the Divine Mysteries on the shore of the 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}Jordan{\*\xmlclose} she was at once transported to the place where she died. The distance which Zosimas had taken twenty days to cover, Mary had evidently traversed in a
n hour and had at once surrendered her soul to God. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Then Zosimas thought: "It is time to do as she wished. But how am I to dig a grave with nothing in my hands?" }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And then he saw nearby a small piece of wood left by some traveler in the desert. Picking 
it up he began to dig the ground. But the earth was hard and dry and did not yield to the efforts of the elder. He grew tired and covered with sweat. He sighed from the depths of his soul and lifting up his eyes he saw a big lion standing close to the sai
n
t's body and licking her feet. At the sight of the lion he trembled with fear, especially when he called to mind Mary's words that she had never seen wild beasts in the desert. But guarding himself with the sign of the cross, the thought came to him that 
the power of the one lying there would protect him and keep him unharmed. Meanwhile the lion drew nearer to him, expressing affection by every movement. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Zosimas said to the lion: }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 "The Great One ordered that her body was to be buried. But I am old and ha
ve not the strength to dig the grave (for I have no spade and it would take too long to go and get one), so can you carry out the work with your claws? Then we can commit to the earth the mortal temple of the saint." }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 While he was still speaking the lion with his front paws began to dig a hole deep enough to bury the body. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 Again the elder washed the feet of the saint with his tears and calling on her to pray for all, covered the body with earth in th
e presence of the lion. It was as it had been, naked and uncovered by anything but the tattered cloak which had been given to her by Zosimas and with which Mary, turning away, had managed to cover part of her body. Then both departed. The lion went off in
t
o the depth of the desert like a lamb, while Zosimas returned to the monastery glorifying and blessing Christ our Lord. And on reaching the monastery he told all the brothers about everything, and all marveled on hearing of God's miracles. And with fear a
nd love they kept the memory of the saint. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
Abbot John, as St. Mary had previously told Abba Zosimas, found a number of things wrong in the monastery and got rid of them with God's help. And Saint Zosimas died in the same monastery, almost attaining the ag
e of a hundred, and passed to eternal life. The monks kept this story without writing it down and passed it on by word of mouth to one another. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 But I (adds Sophronius) as soon as I heard it, wrote it down. Perhaps someone else, better informed, has alrea
dy written the life of the Saint, but as far as I could, I have recorded everything, putting truth above all else. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid3691649 M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
ay God Who works amazing miracles and generously bestows gifts on those who turn to Him with faith, reward those who seek light for themselv
es in this story, who hear, read and are zealous to write it, and may He grant them the lot of blessed Mary together with all who at different times have pleased God by their pious thoughts and labors. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \cs41\f36\cf0\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 And let us also give glory to God, the eternal King,
 that He may grant us too His mercy in the day of judgment for the sake of Jesus Christ our Lord, to Whom belongs all glory, honor, dominion and adoration with the Eternal Father and the Most Holy and Life-giving Spirit, now and always, and though all age
s. Amen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451\charrsid1593147 
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs20\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\f36\insrsid1256504 \page }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid15095451 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \f36\insrsid1065548 
